East Muskingum Board of Education
August 30 at 3:08 PM ·

Student Achievement Showcase 2019-2020 Grand Finale ....

We hope you have enjoyed seeing snippets of just a few of the amazing accomplishments of our Little Muskies which occurred this past school year. Some were face to face & others done remotely, just as our school year begins for 2020-2021.
No matter the location, our students will be engaged in learning information & skills in Academics, Arts, & Athletics which will prepare them for the future.
We appreciate the support of EVERYONE involved in educating our students & look forward to showcasing more Student Achievement in the months to come.
Muskie Pride ♥️
Godspeed!

Matt Abbott, Mike Mathers￼￼, Gail Lash Requardt, Shala Zemba, Renee Coll

shared_text:
East Muskingum Board of Education
August 28 at 6:25 PM ·

In Memoriam:
During the August Board Meeting, former board Member, Kenny McGee, was remembered with a special Honor Table in his memory. Mr. McGee played a very important role on EM Board of Education, serving from 1984-2013, by providing insights from the community & as an avid Muskie Fan.
A moment of silence was held in his memory and, also, for Dot German, long time EM employee, who was especially endeared by staff, students, & families of Perry Elementary School.
The loss of these folks impacts the entire East Muskingum Family.

Matt Abbott, Mike Mathers, Gail Lash Requardt, Shala Zemba, Renee Coll

EMMS football practice will begin on Wednesday August 19. Any 7th and 8th grade student that is interested should report to EMMS that evening. Helmet fitting and practice will run from 5:30-7:30pm, while a parent meeting will be held that same evening at 6:00pm to hand out schedules and discuss pertinent information about the upcoming season.

Please remember that all student athletes must have a current physical on file at the school in order to be able to participate in any school sponsored sports. Students will not be allowed to participate in any on field training/practice until they have a physical turned in.

post_text:
The East Muskingum Administrative Team and staff continue to gather information and plan for the 2020-21 school year. We need your help as we work to finalize "back to school" plans that provide quality instruction and options for our students and parents. In the last two weeks, we have received guidance from both Governor DeWine and the Ohio Department of Education while also working with the Muskingum County Health Department to best prepare for the upcoming school year. We understand that parents must and should make the best decisions for their children.

Therefore, in addition to a traditional school schedule, we are offering a remote learning option led by dedicated East Muskingum teachers based on the number of interested students.

Please respond to this short survey (linked below) to assist in our planning for the upcoming school year.

*Please fill out one survey for each student*

It is with heavy hearts that we remember former Board of Education Member, Mr. Ken McGee. Ken served on the Board for 30 years at East Muskingum Local Schools. Ken will be remembered for his leadership, sense of humor and more than anything, his true passion for our district and community. Our thoughts and prayers are with his wife Julie, children Danielle and Matt and the entire McGee Family. Godspeed

post_text: Cambridge Rotary presented the Dwight L. Dray "Service Above Self" Scholarship Awards at the Cambridge City Park on July 1st. Cambria Beane, (5th from the left) a JGHS graduate, was presented with one of the five awards given. Students were nominated by staff from their respective schools. "Her leadership in the classroom and in her extracurricular activites, as well as her strong work ethic and high moral character" were among the reasons listed for her nomination and selection.

post_text: EMMS will hold cheerleading tryouts at LMIS in the outdoor space between the lower baseball fields and the gymnasium. This location has been selected to insure social distancing and other health precautions are followed. There will also be a clinic held prior to the tryout at the same location on July 7th from 5pm to 7:30pm for 7th grade and July 9th from 5pm to 7:30pm for 8th grade. Try-outs will be July 13th. The athletes will be introduced to the coach and have the chance to learn some basic skills, concepts, and routines that will be included in their tryout. Only students entering 7th or 8th grade for the 2020-2021 school year are eligible to participate. Please RSVP if your child is planning to attend by emailing Taylor Allender at tallender@eastmschools.org

EMMS Boosters
June 15 at 1:14 PM ·

Happy Summer! Hope you all are enjoying this beautiful weather. Many library books are still checked out. A lot of them are thin books like Magic Tree House and Who Was... Those can easily be overlooked in trappers and binders, etc. You can return those books to EMMS at any time in the drop box at the front doors. The box is checked daily and I'll be going in every few days to check them in. If you have any questions, or would like to check out a book for summer reading, please contact me at jbeetem@eastmschools.org. Please feel free to share this message. We'd like to get the books back and the library in order for your return!!!

Many thanks!!
Judy Beetem, Librarian

post_text:
Thank you for your support of East Muskingum Local Schools during the 2019-2020 year. Remote learning in March, April, and May required a monumental team effort between our students, families, and teachers. We are proud of what we accomplished by working together.

As educators across the nation, we are hopeful and optimistic that students will be able to safely return to classrooms in the fall. It is important, however, for us to evaluate our remote learning services to make improvements, in case it is necessary for school buildings to operate in hybrid mode or remotely.

Please take the time to complete the survey below for East Muskingum Schools. We value and appreciate your input. Thank you for your assistance.

Wednesday Evening, May 20th - 5:00p - 7:00p for all students unable to attend their scheduled session.

More details will follow this basic outline as additional plans are made.

Students unable to attend their scheduled period of time are asked to contact the school for additional options.

Please direct any questions or concerns to the John Glenn High School main office at 740-826-7641.

PICK-UP DATE CORRECTION....LMIS procedures for picking up your child’s materials and belongings from school. Each grade level will be scheduled for a different day. If you have multiple children in different grade levels we will try to accommodate you the best that we can.

5th grade will be on Wednesday, May 27th from 2-6 pm.
4th grade will be on Thursday, May 28th from 2-6 pm
3rd grade will be on Friday May 29 from 2-6 pm.

PICKUP STEPS:
- Pull in front of the school where the buses line up.
- Please stay in your car and have the trunk open.
- We will put a bag with your child’s belongings along with an envelope which will contain report cards, certificates, medals and any other important papers in your trunk.

As a reminder...All work needs to be completed and turned in by Saturday May 16th. Also please bring any textbooks or library books with you if you have not already returned them to the school.

5th grade parents….you will be receiving information from the middle school in the mail very soon.

If you have any questions, please call the LMIS office at 740-826-2271.

post_text:
On Monday 4/20/20 Governor DeWine announced that students would not return to school and that remote learning would be in place through the end of the school year.

* Students with internet access in grades 3-12 will continue to receive instruction through Google Classroom.

* Students with no access to the internet and K-2 students will receive additional paper packets next week. More detailed information related to the packets will be released in the coming days.

* All Spring sporting events have been canceled.

* We fully intend to honor the Class of 2020 in some manner and much of that is based on gathering size per the Governor's orders.

Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work together through this crisis.

Updates will be posted to the district website, social media, and the All Call system.

post_text:
An open wireless network has been created for access from all of our school buildings. It does not require a password. Distance from the building can make a difference in signal strength. You can get a decent signal from the parking lot and the signal strength is better the closer to the building you can park. The Middle School and Larry Miller have a much better signal at the rear of the building versus the front of the building.

NOTE: Please remain in your vehicle and adhere to safe social distancing. The WiFi connection utilizes the district web filter for all internet traffic and users must adhere to all district internet policies.

Open wireless network: eastm-open (no password)

East Muskingum Board of Education
January 31 at 12:21 PM ·

Student Art from Larry Miller Intermediate School was displayed at the January Meeting of East Muskingum Board of Education.
In addition, some of these pieces travelled on to Sulens Dental Studio, for the enjoyment of others during these dreary winter days. Visitors are welcome to stop by 750 Princeton Ave. Zanesville, OH to check out the talent of our students. 🤗
